In this we focused on seven learning objectives:

Discover the fundamentals of C++.
Discover when C++ is used in real-life applications.
Learn how to process I/O and manipulate user provided values.
Use header files, class files, and basic programming concepts such as variables and loops.
Discover how pointers and memory management affects our program design.
Learn how to create and destroy dynamic memory objects.
Create sentinel driven programs to mimic a production-grade application.
